cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with rate allocation and routing in energy harvesting networks. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper considers fairness among nodes and time slots, which is a common topic in information theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper focuses on the design of efficient and optimal algorithms for rate allocation and routing. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper deals with energy harvesting networks, which can be seen as a control system. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper considers fairness among nodes, which is a common topic in game theory.
